    "text": "Erdős Problem #812: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Is it true that\\[\\frac{R(n+1)}{R(n)}\\geq 1+c\\]for some constant $c>0$, for all large $n$? Is it true that\\[R(n+1)-R(n) \\gg n^2?\\] Current best: Burr, Erd\\H{o}s, Faudree, and Schelp \\cite{BEFS89} proved that\\[R(n+1)-R(n) \\geq 4n-8\\]for all $n\\geq 2$. The lower bound of [165] implies that\\[R(n+2)-R(n) \\gg n^{2-o(1)}.\\]  References  [BEFS89] Burr, S. Prize: no. OEIS: A059442. Tags: graph theory, ramsey theory.",
